               <msContents>
                  <summary>
                     This anonymous and undated manuscript entitled <title>Risālah-'i Tīrandāzī</title> (Treatise on Archery), was likely completed in 
                     India in the late 18th century. The volume was formerly held in the royal library of the kings of Awadh in Lucknow and bears the seals of 
                     Nāṣir al-Dīn Ḥaydar Shāh (r. 1827–1837) and Amjad ‘Alī Shāh (r. 1842–1847).
                     The same text, under a variant title of <title>Qānūn-i Tīr Andākhtan</title> (The Rules of Archery), 
                     is also found in a composite miscellany manuscript entitled <title>Majmu‘ah-'i Rasā'il</title> (Collection of Treatises) in the Bodleian Library, 
                     (Ouseley Add. 68, folios 421a–424a, see Sachau and Ethe's catalogue, no. 1241).
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_612-item1">
